wikipedia_page.main: Richard  Babington (b Derry 4 February  1869 -  d Ipswich 11 December 1952) was Dean of Cork from 1914 to 1951.Babington was educated at Foyle College and Trinity College, Dublin and ordained in 1892. After a curacy at Drumragh he was the Rector of Moville.His son was Archdeacon of Exeter from 1958 to 1970.
